6quot%3Bgroggy%20and%20tired.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202022%2C%20White%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finfluencer-worried-drinking-less-boring-work-events-life-improved-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edecided%20to%20stop%20drinking%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20hasn't%20done%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Selfie%20of%20four%20women%20wearing%20colored%20sunglasses.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f4ea30c6ad288d147d7eb0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhite%20said%20she%20performs%20better%20at%20work%20now%20she%20is%20sober.%3Cp%3ESam%20White%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20joined%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-sober-non-alcoholic-economy-restaurants-events-boom-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreasing%20number%20of%20people%20choosing%20to%20go%20sober%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F509690%2Fyoung-adults-drinking-less-prior-decades.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eabout%201%2C000%20people%20in%20the%20US%20conducted%20by%20Gallup%20each%20year%20from%202001%20to%202023%20found%20that%20between%202001%20and%202003%2C%2072%25%20of%20adults%20aged%2018%20to%2034%20had%20ever%20drank%20alcohol.%20This%20dropped%20to%2062%25%20between%202021%20and%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20volume%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falcohol-brands-preparing-growing-nonalcoholic-market-heineken-constellation-anheuser-busch-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enon-alcoholic%20beer%20and%20cider%20sold%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20the%20US%20grew%20by%2030%25%20between%202022%20and%202023%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20IWSR%2C%20a%20market%20analysis%20firm%20specializing%20in%20drinks%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220b67d519-7866-4ccb-bf79-89c7097bb5ea%5C%22%3EWhite%20stopped%20drinking%20without%20a%20'rock%20bottom'%20moment%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhite%20said%20she%20didn't%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Brock%20bottom%20moment%26quot%3B%20that%20was%20the%20catalyst%20for%20her%20quitting%20drinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%20do%20you%20need%20to%20have%20a%20rock%20bottom%20moment%20to%20make%20a%20choice%20for%20yourself%20that%20is%20very%20empowering%20and%20makes%20you%20feel%20so%20much%20better%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20there%20are%20a%20few%20reasons%20White%20stopped%20drinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20feared%20she%20was%20at%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20having%20a%20problem%20with%20alcohol%20because%20her%20mother%20had%20abused%20it%20for%20years.%20Research%20shows%20that%20people%20whose%20family%20members%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fovercoming-alcohol-use-disorder%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealcohol%20use%20disorder%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20experience%20it%20themselves%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20that's%20because%20of%20a%20genetic%20predisposition%2C%20environmental%20influences%2C%20or%20exposure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20her%20dad%20received%20a%20terminal%20diagnosis%2C%20White%20said%20she%20was%20mindful%20of%20the%20emotional%20impact%20the%20inevitable%20grief%20would%20have%20on%20her%20drinking%2C%20because%20she'd%20seen%20her%20mom%20go%20from%20a%20heavy%20drinker%20to%20an%20alcoholic%20when%20experiencing%20grief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20want%20to%20have%20something%20in%20my%20life%20that%20would%20enable%20me%20to%20emotionally%20switch%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI've%20got%20two%20kids.%20I%20want%20to%20be%20the%20best%20version%20of%20myself%20for%20them%2C%20so%20I%20just%20decided%20that%20it%20was%20the%20right%20time%20to%20just%20call%20it%20a%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Freproductive-health%2Fperimenopause-symptoms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapproaching%20menopause%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20wanted%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20she%20could%20change%20to%20give%20her%20as%20much%20vitality%20and%20energy%20as%20possible%20as%20her%20hormones%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20quite%20a%20bit%20of%20research%20coming%20out%20now%20on%20the%20impact%20of%20alcohol%20on%20women%20and%20cancers%2C%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20In%202019%2C%2016.4%25%20of%20approximately%20270%2C000%20breast%20cancer%20cases%20in%20women%20were%20linked%20to%20alcohol%20consumption%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falcohol-cancer-risk-surgeon-general-report-smoking-cigarettes-obesity-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%20released%20earlier%20this%20year%20by%20the%20US%20Surgeon%20General%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d644f538-8761-4a75-b278-fc631ba4ff9d%5C%22%3EQuitting%20drinking%20made%20dealing%20with%20stress%20easier%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20tolerance%20for%20handling%20stress%20is%20substantially%20better%20now%20than%20it%20was%2C%26quot%3B%20White%20said%20of%20life%20after%20alcohol.%20%26quot%3BEverything%20felt%20so%20much%20more%20overwhelming%20on%20a%20day%20with%20a%20hangover.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20work%2C%20she%20is%20more%20productive%20and%20excited%20about%20new%20projects.%20Her%20performance%20is%20better%2C%20too%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20networking%2C%20she%20is%20more%20selective%20about%20the%20events%20she%20attends.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20to%20be%20interesting%20and%20fun%20in%20its%20own%20right.%20If%20it%20needs%20booze%20to%20make%20it%20tolerable%2C%20I%20wouldn't%20go%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhite%20also%20feels%20like%20she%20has%20her%20weekends%20back.%20Instead%20of%20waking%20up%20late%20after%20nights%20spent%20drinking%2C%20she%20has%20time%20for%20self-care%2C%20hikes%2C%20massages%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ffitness%2Fice-bath%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eice%20baths%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20now%20the%20fittest%20I've%20ever%20been%20in%20my%20life%20and%20I'm%20coming%20up%20to%2050%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20did%20a%20personal%20best%20of%20a%20120%20kg%20squat%20the%20other%20day%2C%20which%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20able%20to%20do%20when%20I%20was%2026.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hardest%20thing%20is%20socializing%20around%20people%20who%20drink%20heavily%2C%20as%20it%20can%20feel%20as%20though%20there's%20a%20%26quot%3Bdisconnect%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFinding%20friendships%20and%20dynamics%20where%20you%20can%20socialize%20and%20enjoy%20people's%20company%20without%20alcohol%20was%20the%20biggest%20struggle%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20I%20feel%20better%20every%20day%20now%20than%20I%20ever%20felt%20when%20I%20drank%20alcohol.%20No%20question%2C%20everything%20is%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-quit-drinking-alcohol-fitter-less-groggy-manage-stress-weekends-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744112755000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f4e9c43fe8d392836267c2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-quit-drinking-alcohol-fitter-less-groggy-manage-stress-weekends-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sam%20White%2C%20a%20CEO%2C%20would%20drag%20herself%20through%20Mondays%20after%20drinking%20on%20weekends.%20She%20quit%20to%20become%20the%20best%20version%20of%20herself%20at%20work%20and%2