ravin-jesuthasan-why-companies-enforce-rto-mandates-future-of-work-2024-8%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworkplace%20in%20flux%3C%2Fa%3E%20amid%20the%20AI%20boom.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAI%20could%20be%20closing%20knowledge%20gaps%20and%20changing%20how%20teams%20collaborate%2C%20one%20working%20paper%20found.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGen%20Z%20workers%20and%20engineers%20surveyed%20were%20divided%20on%20whether%20AI%20is%20helping%20or%20hurting%20their%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20over%20two%20years%20since%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-chat-gpt-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20introduced%20to%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20workplace%20is%20still%20figuring%20out%20how%20to%20adapt%20to%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20large-scale%20field%20experiment%20and%20two%20surveys%20published%20or%20conducted%20last%20month%20give%20some%20clues%20into%20how%20AI%20is%20reshaping%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20AI%20has%20shown%20signs%20of%20helping%20close%20experience%20gaps%20and%20improve%20collaboration%2C%20the%20data%20suggests%20some%20workers%20are%20skeptical%20and%20cautious%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20when%20guidance%20on%20how%20to%20use%20AI%20is%20limited%20or%20unclear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20researchers%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22572ab0f9-a476-4363-839b-39c447a84c08%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAI%20can%20be%20a%20useful%20teammate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20using%20AI%20performed%20just%20as%20well%20as%20two-person%20human%20teams%2C%20and%20AI-augmented%20teams%20were%20significantly%20more%20likely%20to%20produce%20top-tier%20solutions%2C%20a%20working%20paper%20has%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20pre-registered%2C%20randomized%20controlled%20trial%20involving%20776%20professionals%20at%20Procter%20%26amp%3B%20Gamble%2C%20researchers%20from%20Harvard%2C%20Wharton%2C%20and%20the%20Digital%20Data%20Design%20Institute%20assigned%20participants%20to%20complete%20real-world%20product%20development%20tasks.%20They%20included%20generating%20packaging%20ideas%20and%20proposing%20retail%20strategies%2C%20either%20with%20or%20without%20the%20help%20of%20GPT-4%20or%20GPT-4o.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParticipants%20were%20randomly%20placed%20into%20one%20of%20four%20groups%3A%20working%20solo%20or%20in%20teams%2C%20and%20with%20or%20without%20AI%20access.%20The%20study%20measured%20solution%20quality%2C%20task%20completion%20time%2C%20and%20emotional%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20our%20new%20paper%20on%20using%20AI%20solving%20real%20business%20problems%20at%20Procter%20and%20Gamble%20where%20we%20found%20AI%20helped%20individuals%2C%20even%20inexperienced%20ones%2C%20perform%20as%20well%20as%20teams%20of%20two%2C%20we%20gave%20participants%20a%20set%20of%20default%20prompts%20to%20work%20with.%20Here%20some%20are%3A%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FIbV6VbHZ8p%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FIbV6VbHZ8p%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FvhyvOoZkLm%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FvhyvOoZkLm%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Ethan%20Mollick%20(%40emollick)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Femollick%2Fstatus%2F1904340100412313631%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%2025%2C%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIndividuals%20using%20AI%20performed%20as%20well%20as%20human%20teams%20working%20without%20AI%2C%20the%20study%20found%2C%20and%20AI-assisted%20teams%20performed%20best%20overall%20and%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20generate%20the%20top%2010%25%20of%20solutions%20than%20those%20working%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEthan%20Mollick%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20UPenn's%20Wharton%20School%20and%20one%20of%20the%20paper's%20authors%2C%20said%20in%20a%20March%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oneusefulthing.org%2Fp%2Fthe-cybernetic-teammate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblog%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20findings%20suggest%20%26quot%3BAI%20sometimes%20functions%20more%20like%20a%20teammate%20than%20a%20tool%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20this%20should%20make%20companies%20think%20differently%20about%20the%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20businesses%20should%20rethink%20how%20they%20structure%20teams%2C%20train%20workers%2C%20and%20assign%20cross-functional%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20also%20found%20that%20when%20given%20access%20to%20AI%2C%20employees%20with%20less%20product%20development%20experience%20performed%20at%20levels%20comparable%20to%20veteran%20teams%2C%20suggesting%20the%20technology%20can%20help%20close%20functional%20knowledge%20gaps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20with%20AI%20improved%20the%20emotional%20experience%20of%20work%2C%20the%20study%20suggested.%20Participants%20using%20AI%20reported%20higher%20levels%20of%20excitement%2C%20energy%2C%20and%20enthusiasm%20and%20lower%20levels%20of%20anxiety%20and%20frustration%20compared%20to%20those%20working%20without%20it.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20individuals%20working%20with%20AI%20had%20more%20positive%20emotional%20responses%20than%20those%20working%20in%20human%20teams.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhile%20the%20experiment%20involved%20just%20one%20day%20of%20work%2C%20the%20paper%20is%20still%20a%20working%20draft%20and%20hasn't%20yet%20been%20peer-reviewed.%20The%20researchers%20acknowledge%20caveats%3A%20the%20study%20involved%20only%20small%20teams%20participating%20in%20just%20one%20day%20of%20tasks%2C%20and%20relied%20on%20GPT-4%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225586fcb6-4b9b-481c-8dc6-e1e513aecbe5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMost%20Gen%20Z%20workers%20say%20they%20lack%20AI%20guidance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20digital%20natives%2C%20most%20Gen%20Z%20workers%20are%20navigating%20AI%20at%20work%20without%20clear%20guidance%2C%20a%20March%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gallup.com%2Fanalytics%2F651674%2Fgen-z-research.aspx%3Fthank-you-report-form%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Gallup%20and%20the%20Walton%20Family%20Foundation%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20half%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-avoid-company-social-events-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%3C%2Fa%3E%20workers%20%E2%80%94%2055%25%20%E2%80%94%20said%20their%20employers%20have%20no%20formal%20policy%20on%20AI%20use.%20And%20among%20those%20whose%20workplaces%20do%20have%20rules%2C%20only%20about%20one%20in%2010%20describe%20those%20policies%20as%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20clear.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Gallup%20web%20survey%20of%203%2C465%2013-to%2028-year-old%20Americans%20across%20all%2050%20US%20states%20said%20that%20Gen%20Z%20students%20and%20employees%20in%20environments%20with%20clear%20AI%20guidelines%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20use%20AI%20regularly%20than%20their%20peers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20many%20younger%20workers%20are%20skeptical%20about%20the%20quality%20of%20AI-generated%20work.%20Nearly%20two-thirds%20of%20Gen%20Z%20respondents%20said%20they'd%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20trust%20human-produced%20work%20compared%20to%20work%20done%20or%20assisted%20by%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20paint%20a%20conflicted%20picture%20of%20how%20Gen%20Z%20as%20a%20whole%20perceives%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chatgpt-brainstorming-addiction-dependence-negative-consequences-mit-research-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI's%20impact%20on%20their%20critical%20thinking%3C%2Fa%3E%20versus%20their%20efficiency%20at%20work%20or%20school.%20N