cond-hottest%20March%20in%20the%20Copernicus%20dataset%2C%20sustaining%20a%20near-unbroken%20spell%20of%20record%20or%20near-record-breaking%20temperatures%20that%20has%20persisted%20since%20July%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20virtually%20every%20month%20has%20been%20at%20least%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20hotter%20than%20it%20was%20before%20the%20industrial%20revolution%2C%20when%20humans%20began%20burning%20massive%20amounts%20of%20coal%2C%20oil%20and%20gas.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMarch%20was%201.6C%20above%20pre-industrial%20times%2C%20extending%20an%20anomaly%20so%20unusual%20that%20scientists%20are%20still%20trying%20to%20fully%20explain%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20we're%20still%20at%201.6C%20above%20preindustrial%20is%20indeed%20remarkable%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Friederike%20Otto%20of%20the%20Grantham%20Institute%20for%20Climate%20Change%20and%20the%20Environment%20at%20Imperial%20College%20London.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20very%20firmly%20in%20the%20grip%20of%20human-caused%20climate%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20had%20predicted%20the%20extreme%20run%20of%20global%20temperatures%20would%20subside%20after%20a%20warming%20El%20Nino%20event%20peaked%20in%20early%202024%2C%20but%20they%20have%20stubbornly%20lingered%20well%20into%202025.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20still%20experiencing%20extremely%20high%20temperatures%20worldwide.%20This%20is%20an%20exceptional%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20Robert%20Vautard%2C%20a%20leading%20scientist%20with%20the%20United%20Nations'%20climate%20expert%20panel%20IPCC%2C%20told%20AFP.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Climate%20breakdown'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20warn%20that%20every%20fraction%20of%20a%20degree%20of%20global%20warming%20increases%20the%20intensity%20and%20frequency%20of%20extreme%20weather%20events%20such%20as%20heatwaves%2C%20heavy%20rainfall%20and%20droughts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClimate%20change%20is%20not%20just%20about%20rising%20temperatures%20but%20the%20knock-on%20effect%20of%20all%20that%20extra%20heat%20being%20trapped%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20and%20seas%20by%20greenhouse%20gases%20like%20carbon%20dioxide%20and%20methane.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWarmer%20seas%20mean%20higher%20evaporation%20and%20greater%20moisture%20in%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20causing%20heavier%20deluges%20and%20feeding%20energy%20into%20storms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20also%20affects%20global%20rainfall%20patterns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMarch%20in%20Europe%20was%200.26C%20above%20the%20previous%20hottest%20record%20for%20the%20month%20set%20in%202014%2C%20Copernicus%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20parts%20of%20the%20continent%20experienced%20the%20%26quot%3Bdriest%20March%20on%20record%20and%20others%20their%20wettest%26quot%3B%20for%20about%20half%20a%20century%2C%20said%20Samantha%20Burgess%20of%20the%20European%20Centre%20for%20Medium-Range%20Weather%20Forecasts%2C%20which%20runs%20the%20Copernicus%20climate%20monitor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBill%20McGuire%2C%20a%20climate%20scientist%20from%20University%20College%20London%2C%20said%20the%20contrasting%20extremes%20%26quot%3Bshows%20clearly%20how%20a%20destabilised%20climate%20means%20more%20and%20bigger%20weather%20extremes%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20climate%20breakdown%20progresses%2C%20more%20broken%20records%20are%20only%20to%20be%20expected%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElsewhere%20in%20March%2C%20scientists%20said%20that%20climate%20change%20intensified%20a%20blistering%20heatwave%20across%20Central%20Asia%20and%20fuelled%20conditions%20for%20extreme%20rainfall%20which%20killed%2016%20people%20in%20Argentina.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPuzzling%20heat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spectacular%20surge%20in%20global%20heat%20pushed%202023%20and%20then%202024%20to%20become%20the%20hottest%20years%20on%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%20was%20also%20the%20first%20full%20calendar%20year%20to%20exceed%201.5C%20--%20the%20safer%20warming%20limit%20agreed%20by%20most%20nations%20under%20the%20Paris%20climate%20accord.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20single%20year%20breach%20does%20not%20represent%20a%20permanent%20crossing%20of%20the%201.5C%20threshold%2C%20which%20is%20measured%20over%20decades%2C%20but%20scientists%20have%20warned%20the%20goal%20is%20slipping%20out%20of%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Copernicus%2C%20global%20warming%20reached%20an%20estimated%201.36C%20above%20pre-industrial%20levels%20in%20October%20last%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%2030-year%20trend%20leading%20up%20to%20then%20continued%2C%20the%20world%20would%20hit%201.5C%20by%20June%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20are%20unanimous%20that%20burning%20fossil%20fuels%20has%20largely%20driven%20long-term%20global%20warming%2C%20and%20that%20natural%20climate%20variability%20can%20also%20influence%20temperatures%20from%20one%20year%20to%20the%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20they%20are%20less%20certain%20about%20what%20else%20might%20have%20contributed%20to%20this%20record%20heat%20spike%2C%20or%20how%20this%20impacts%20our%20understanding%20about%20how%20climate%20might%20behave%20in%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVautard%20said%20there%20were%20%26quot%3Bphenomena%20that%20remain%20to%20be%20explained%26quot%3B%20but%20the%20exceptional%20temperatures%20still%20fell%20within%20the%20upper%20range%20of%20scientific%20projections%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20think%20changes%20in%20global%20cloud%20patterns%2C%20airborne%20pollution%20and%20Earth's%20ability%20to%20store%20carbon%20in%20natural%20sinks%20like%20forests%20and%20oceans%20could%20be%20among%20factors%20contributing%20to%20the%20planet%20overheating.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECopernicus%20uses%20billions%20of%20measurements%20from%20satellites%2C%20ships%2C%20aircraft%20and%20weather%20stations%20to%20aid%20its%20climate%20calculations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20records%20go%20back%20to%201940%20but%20other%20sources%20of%20climate%20data%20--%20such%20as%20ice%20cores%2C%20tree%20rings%20and%20coral%20skeletons%20--%20allow%20scientists%20to%20expand%20their%20conclusions%20using%20evidence%20from%20much%20further%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20say%20the%20current%20period%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20the%20warmest%20the%20Earth%20has%20been%20for%20the%20last%20125%2C000%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744109400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2Fdcafsp78_europe-heat_625x300_08_April_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fglobal-temperatures-at-historic-highs-europe-records-hottest-march-ever-8116159%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Global%20temperatures%20hovered%20at%20historic%20highs%20in%20March%2C%20Europe's%20climate%20monitor%20said%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20prolonging%20an%20unprecedented%20heat%20streak%20that%20has%20pushed%20the%20bounds%20of%20scientific%20explanation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fglobal-temperatures-at-historic-highs-europe-records-hottest-march-ever-8116159%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Raid%202%20trailer%20reactions%3A%20Netizens%20call%20it%20%E2%80%98masterpiece%E2%80%99%20already%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744109270000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-120093529%2Cimgsize-779514.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fraid-2-trailer-reactions-netizens-call-ajay-devgn-and-riteish-deshmukhs-film-a-masterpiece-already-while-