0assessed%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsatellite-photos-show-how-russian-forces-have-surrounded-ukraine-2022-2%23brestsky-training-area-belarus-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussia%20had%20moved%20military%20equipment%20and%20soldiers%20to%20borders%20along%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20Ukrainians%20were%20preparing%20the%20troops%20and%20civilians%20for%20an%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20invaded%20on%20February%2024%2C%202022%2C%20bombarding%20Ukraine%20and%20launching%20assaults%20aimed%20at%20swiftly%20seizing%20Kyiv.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShuttering%20the%20embassy%20in%20those%20early%20days%20before%20Russia's%20invasion%20began%20wasn't%20as%20simple%20as%20turning%20off%20the%20lights%20and%20locking%20the%20doors.%20VanAntwerp%20and%20his%20team%20had%20to%20destroy%20any%20and%20all%20sensitive%20information%20to%20prevent%20it%20from%20falling%20into%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20Russian%20army.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20part%20of%20you%20in%20the%20moment%20that's%20like%2C%20'I%20don't%20really%20know%20what%20I'm%20doing%2C'%26quot%3B%20VanAntwerp%2C%20now%20the%20director%20of%20US%20Army%20Special%20Operations%20Command's%20Capability%20Development%20Integration%20Directorate%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etold%20BI%20during%20last%20week's%20USASOC%20Capabilities%20Exercise%20at%20Fort%20Bragg%20in%20North%20Carolina.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20back%20of%20a%20black%20helicopter%20is%20seen%20as%20US%20Army%20Rangers%20slide%20down%20ropes%20onto%20a%20beige%20building.%20The%20sky%20is%20overcast.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f4293a3fe8d39283625b13%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Army%20rangers%20fast%20rope%20off%20a%20MH-47%20Chinook%20as%20part%20of%20an%20airborne%20assault%20demonstration.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20photo%20by%20Sgt.%20Benjamin%20D.%20Castro%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EVanAntwerp%20got%20the%20call%20in%20early%202022%20to%20shuffle%20his%20forces%20out%20of%20Kyiv.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20he%20and%20his%20team%20took%20over%20embassy%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%2010th%20Special%20Forces%20Group%20had%20built%20trust%20with%20the%20Ukrainian%20military%20after%20long%20working%20with%20its%20operators%20since%20Russia's%20initial%20invasion%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20goal%20for%20the%20US%20special%20operations%20advisors%20stationed%20in%20the%20country%20had%20been%20to%20help%20Ukrainian%20operators%20break%20away%20from%20their%20Soviet-style%20approaches%20and%20adopt%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emore%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwestern-weapons-f-16-abrams-likely-wont-survive-ukraine-experts-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWestern-style%20methods%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20changing%20how%20the%20individual%20soldier%20and%20the%20critical%20non-commissioned%20officer%20make%20battlefield%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20going%20to%20say%20we%20transformed%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20VanAntwerp%20explained%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bit%20was%20a%20big%20contributor%20to%20how%20they%20thought%20and%20how%20their%20SOF%20operated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmpowered%20NCOs%20have%20given%20Ukraine%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-forces-cant-cope-with-ukrainian-ncos-enlisted-leader-says-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecombat%20and%20decision-making%20flexibility%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20is%20vastly%20different%20from%20Russia's%20top-down%20approach%20that%20requires%20generals%20for%20battlefield%20decision-making%2C%20keeping%20them%20close%20to%20the%20front%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20was%20time%20to%20evacuate%20the%20embassy%20and%20shutter%20it%2C%20VanAntwerp%20got%20the%20call%20because%20of%20the%20relationship%20he%20and%20his